        },
        {
          "label": "(17)",
          "token": "17",
          "kind": "numeric",
          "text": "Nominal electric generating capacity means the maximum net electric power output of an energy facility based on the average temperature, barometric pressure and relative humidity at the site during the times of the year when the facility is intended to operate.",
